n\\n### Positive aspects\\n\\n- **Well-scoped**: The PR correctly identifies that hook code paths should use structured logging while user-facing command paths should keep stderr. The boundary is clearly drawn.\\n- **Dead code removal**: `StageFiles` and `StageFilesContext`/`StageForSession`/`StageForTask` are genuinely unused. Clean deletion.\\n- **Privacy fix**: The commit message content was being logged directly; now logs only `message_length`. Good catch (addressed in 324b230c).\\n- **Duplicate log fix**: The subagent start/end handlers had two overlapping `logging.Info` calls after the conversion. Merged into single calls (324b230c).\\n- **push_common.go correctly reverted**: Pre-push hook output is visible to users during `git push`, so keeping stderr there is the right call.\\n\\n### Issues found\\n\\n#### 1. `CalculateTokenUsage` silently swallows errors with no logging (Low severity)\\n\\n`token_usage.go` now drops errors entirely - no stderr, no structured logging, nothing. Every other function in this PR replaces `fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr)` with `logging.Warn/Debug`; this one just deletes the diagnostics. The comment says \\\"stderr is unreliable\\\" but the fix should be structured logging, not silence.\\n\\nThe function doesn't accept `context.Context`, but callers (`lifecycle.go:374`, `manual_commit_condensation.go:495,539`) all have `ctx` available. Consider either:\\n- Adding a `ctx` parameter and using `logging.Debug` for errors, or\\n- At minimum adding a comment explaining why errors are intentionally invisible (not just unreliable-stderr)\\n\\nThe current doc comment is close (\\\"Errors are silently ignored because this runs in agent hook paths where stderr is unreliable\\\") but the fix for \\\"unreliable stderr\\\" everywhere else was structured logging, not silence.\\n\\n#### 2. `logFileChanges` lost individual file names (Low severity, intentional?)\\n\\nThe old `logFileChanges` listed each modified/new/deleted file by name. The new version only logs counts:\\n\\n```go\\nlogging.Debug(logCtx, \\\"files changed during session\\\",\\n    slog.Int(\\\"modified\\\", len(modified)),\\n    slog.Int(\\\"new\\\", len(newFiles)),\\n    slog.Int(\\\"deleted\\\", len(deleted)))\\n```\\n\\nThis makes debugging harder when a checkpoint includes unexpected files. Consider logging the file lists as a single `slog.Any(\\\"files\\\", ...)` attribute, or at least adding a separate `Debug` call with file names when total changes are below some threshold.\\n\\n#### 3. `EnsureMetadataBranch` still uses `context.Background()` (from Copilot's suppressed comment - still valid)\\n\\nLooking at `common.go:282`, `EnsureMetadataBranch` doesn't accept `context.Context`. This isn't a regression from this PR (the function already existed without context), but the PR description says \\\"User-facing commands keep their stderr prints unchanged\\\" - and `EnsureMetadataBranch` *does* still print to stderr (correctly preserved in 324b230c). No action needed now, but worth noting as a future improvement.\\n\\n#### 4. Minor: `IsAncestorOf` signature change is unrelated\\n\\nThe diff in `common.go` shows `IsAncestorOf` gained a `ctx context.Context` parameter with cancellation checking. This seems unrelated to the logging PR (likely from a merge with main). Not a problem, just noting it wasn't mentioned in the PR description.\\n\\n### Style / consistency\\n\\n- Logging levels are well-chosen: `Warn` for failures that affect functionality, `Info` for operational events, `Debug` for detailed tracing.\\n- `slog.String(\\\"error\\\", err.Error())` pattern is used consistently (vs `slog.Any(\\\"error\\\", err)`). This is fine and consistent with the codebase.\\n- Component names in `logging.WithComponent()` are appropriate and match existing patterns.\\n\\n### Summary\\n\\nThe PR is well-executed and the review-address commit handles most feedback. The main remaining item is the silent error swallowing in `CalculateTokenUsage` - it should use structured logging like everything else in this PR rather than dropping diagnostics entirely. The file list loss in `logFileChanges` is a minor debuggability concern.\\n\\n**Recommendation**: Address the `CalculateTokenUsage` logging gap, then this is ready to merge.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":3199,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":71347,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":3199},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYYLM3BvqcYS6QwdMToig\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"8a490b70-a060-4741-b674-0923e0b81680\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-27T09:26:51.605Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"8a490b70-a060-4741-b674-0923e0b81680\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/robin/Developer/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"c1a2d60e-e783-458b-93d8-3fee2a05a02b\",\"version\":\"2.1.49\",\"gitBranch\":\"gtrrz-victor/replace-fmt-with-log-inside-agent-hooks\",\"slug\":\"spicy-mapping-raven\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"c7072036-cfba-487e-a4e7-16c87fc54558\",\"toolUseID\":\"c7072036-cfba-487e-a4e7-16c87fc54558\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-27T09:26:51.771Z\",\"uuid\":\"dad96fb2-79e3-47a0-a519-903bf444c7da\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"dad96fb2-79e3-47a0-a519-903bf444c7da\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/robin/Developer/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"c1a2d60e-e783-458b-93d8-3fee2a05a02b\",\"version\":\"2.1.49\",\"gitBranch\":\"gtrrz-victor/replace-fmt-with-log-inside-agent-hooks\",\"slug\":\"spicy-mapping-raven\",\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"stop_hook_summary\",\"hookCount\":1,\"hookInfos\":[{\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\",\"durationMs\":54